gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 145, Raptors 101
gameRecap.excerpt: The Knicks defeated the Raptors, 145-101. Miles McBride led the way for the Knicks with a career-high tying 29 points, along with a career-high nine 3PM for the Knicks, while Jalen Brunson added 26 points, four rebounds and seven assists in the victory. Gradey Dick tallied a career-high 23 points for the Raptors in the losing effort. The Knicks win their third game in a row as they improve to 44-28 on the season, while the Raptors have dropped 12-straight games and fall to 23-50.
